     - 3 vertices/sides: triangle (J)
     - 4 vertices/sides: kite (D) if matching kite properties, else map using other options such as trapezoid (K) or omitted if not in options
     - 5 vertices/sides: pentagon (G)
     - 6 vertices/sides: hexagon (C)
     - 7 vertices/sides: heptagon (B)
     - 8 vertices/sides: octagon (F)
   - Specific figures:
     - Kite (D): a quadrilateral with two pairs of adjacent sides of equal length, not just any 4-sided figure.
     - Trapezoid (K): a quadrilateral with at least one pair of parallel sides.
   - Other Figures:
     - Line (E): a single straight segment.
     - Sector (I): a "pizza-slice" shape of a circle.
     - Ellipse (K): if the path uses elliptical arc ("A" command) forming a non-circular oval.

