- (C) hexagon — 6 sides/vertices
- (D) kite — quadrilateral with two distinct pairs of adjacent equal-length sides
- (E) line — two points with no area
- (F) octagon — 8 sides/vertices
- (G) pentagon — 5 sides/vertices
- (H) rectangle — quadrilateral with four right angles and opposite sides equal
- (I) sector — wedge or 'pie-slice' portion of a circle, typically defined by two radii and an arc
- (J) triangle — 3 sides/vertices
- (K) trapezoid — quadrilateral with at least one pair of parallel sides (may include rectangles unless a more specific label is possible; may also be used for ellipse if 'ellipse' is specified as (K))

**4. Task Procedure:**  
