      - (C): Hexagon (6 sides/vertices)
      - (D): Kite (special 4-sided polygon, two pairs of adjacent equal sides, diagonals perpendicular, axis of symmetry)
      - (E): Line (single straight segment)
      - (F): Octagon (8 sides/vertices)
      - (G): Pentagon (5 sides/vertices)
      - (H): Rectangle (4 sides, all right angles, opposite sides equal)
      - (I): Sector (portion/slice of a circle/ellipse, bounded by two radii and an arc)
      - (J): Triangle (3 sides/vertices)
      - (K): Ellipse

