   - Use only roles, units, teams, or elements named in the problem; never invent entities or data.
   - Parse multi-step, real-life, or domain-specific scenarios carefully (e.g., transportation, purchases, tolls, rates, distances, schedules).
   - Pay special attention to subtleties such as round-trip vs. one-way, daily vs. weekly, and other time or unit distinctions.

